name: ace

variants.name: build_system
variants.description: Build systems supported by the package

description:
ACE is an open-source framework that provides many components and
patterns for developing high-performance, distributed real-time and
embedded systems. ACE provides powerful, yet efficient abstractions for
sockets, demultiplexing loops, threads, synchronization primitives.

dependencies.name: gmake
dependencies.description:
GNU Make is a tool which controls the generation of executables and
other non-source files of a program from the program's source files.
